Bell Media's lower capital expenditures in 2019 can be attributed to the following:
• The continued roll-out of fixed WTTP to rural and remote locations in Ontario and Québec, which continues to expand our fibre internet network and bring fibre TV services to more homes and businesses;
• The continued deployment of FTTP in our wireless network, which supports the deployment of 5G technology and continues to increase network speed, coverage and signal quality;
• The continued investment in our fibre backhaul network, which is providing us with the capacity to deliver fibre internet services and fibre TV services in rural and remote areas, as well as support the development of a new, faster fibre backhaul network to support 5G technology and the roll-out of fixed WTTP;
• The continued development of our global voice network, which is being deployed in collaboration with other Bell companies to support the roll-out of fixed WTTP.
